49 const std::string LOGNAME = "trajectory_processing.time_optimal_trajectory_generation";
50 constexpr double EPS = 0.000001;
51 class LinearPathSegment : public PathSegment
52 {
53 public:
54  LinearPathSegment(const Eigen::VectorXd& start, const Eigen::VectorXd& end)
55  : PathSegment((end - start).norm()), end_(end), start_(start)
56  {
57  }
58 
59  Eigen::VectorXd getConfig(double s) const override
60  {
61  s /= length_;
62  s = std::max(0.0, std::min(1.0, s));
63  return (1.0 - s) * start_ + s * end_;
64  }
65 
66  Eigen::VectorXd getTangent(double /* s */) const override
67  {
68  return (end_ - start_) / length_;
69  }
70 
71  Eigen::VectorXd getCurvature(double /* s */) const override
72  {
73  return Eigen::VectorXd::Zero(start_.size());
74  }
75 
76  std::list<double> getSwitchingPoints() const override
77  {
78  return std::list<double>();
79  }
80 
81  LinearPathSegment* clone() const override
82  {
83  return new LinearPathSegment(*this);
84  }
85 
86 private:
87  Eigen::VectorXd end_;
88  Eigen::VectorXd start_;
89 };

91 class CircularPathSegment : public PathSegment
92 {
93 public:
94  CircularPathSegment(const Eigen::VectorXd& start, const Eigen::VectorXd& intersection, const Eigen::VectorXd& end,
95  double max_deviation)
96  {
97  if ((intersection - start).norm() < 0.000001 || (end - intersection).norm() < 0.000001)
98  {
99  length_ = 0.0;
100  radius = 1.0;
101  center = intersection;
102  x = Eigen::VectorXd::Zero(start.size());
103  y = Eigen::VectorXd::Zero(start.size());
104  return;
105  }
106 
107  const Eigen::VectorXd start_direction = (intersection - start).normalized();
108  const Eigen::VectorXd end_direction = (end - intersection).normalized();
109 
110  if ((start_direction - end_direction).norm() < 0.000001)
111  {
112  length_ = 0.0;
113  radius = 1.0;
114  center = intersection;
115  x = Eigen::VectorXd::Zero(start.size());
116  y = Eigen::VectorXd::Zero(start.size());
117  return;
118  }
119 
120  // directions must be different at this point so angle is always non-zero
121  const double angle = acos(std::max(-1.0, start_direction.dot(end_direction)));
122  const double start_distance = (start - intersection).norm();
123  const double end_distance = (end - intersection).norm();
124 
125  // enforce max deviation
126  double distance = std::min(start_distance, end_distance);
127  distance = std::min(distance, max_deviation * sin(0.5 * angle) / (1.0 - cos(0.5 * angle)));
128 
129  radius = distance / tan(0.5 * angle);
130  length_ = angle * radius;
131 
132  center = intersection + (end_direction - start_direction).normalized() * radius / cos(0.5 * angle);
133  x = (intersection - distance * start_direction - center).normalized();
134  y = start_direction;
135  }
136 
137  Eigen::VectorXd getConfig(double s) const override
138  {
139  const double angle = s / radius;
140  return center + radius * (x * cos(angle) + y * sin(angle));
141  }
142 
143  Eigen::VectorXd getTangent(double s) const override
144  {
145  const double angle = s / radius;
146  return -x * sin(angle) + y * cos(angle);
147  }
148 
149  Eigen::VectorXd getCurvature(double s) const override
150  {
151  const double angle = s / radius;
152  return -1.0 / radius * (x * cos(angle) + y * sin(angle));
153  }
154 
155  std::list<double> getSwitchingPoints() const override
156  {
157  std::list<double> switching_points;
158  const double dim = x.size();
159  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < dim; ++i)
160  {
161  double switching_angle = atan2(y[i], x[i]);
162  if (switching_angle < 0.0)
163  {
164  switching_angle += M_PI;
165  }
166  const double switching_point = switching_angle * radius;
167  if (switching_point < length_)
168  {
169  switching_points.push_back(switching_point);
170  }
171  }
172  switching_points.sort();
173  return switching_points;
174  }
175 
176  CircularPathSegment* clone() const override
177  {
178  return new CircularPathSegment(*this);
179  }
180 
181 private:
182  double radius;
183  Eigen::VectorXd center;
184  Eigen::VectorXd x;
185  Eigen::VectorXd y;
186 };

188 Path::Path(const std::list<Eigen::VectorXd>& path, double max_deviation) : length_(0.0)
189 {
190  if (path.size() < 2)
191  return;
192  std::list<Eigen::VectorXd>::const_iterator path_iterator1 = path.begin();
193  std::list<Eigen::VectorXd>::const_iterator path_iterator2 = path_iterator1;
194  ++path_iterator2;
195  std::list<Eigen::VectorXd>::const_iterator path_iterator3;
196  Eigen::VectorXd start_config = *path_iterator1;
197  while (path_iterator2 != path.end())
198  {
199  path_iterator3 = path_iterator2;
200  ++path_iterator3;
201  if (max_deviation > 0.0 && path_iterator3 != path.end())
202  {
203  CircularPathSegment* blend_segment =
204  new CircularPathSegment(0.5 * (*path_iterator1 + *path_iterator2), *path_iterator2,
205  0.5 * (*path_iterator2 + *path_iterator3), max_deviation);
206  Eigen::VectorXd end_config = blend_segment->getConfig(0.0);
207  if ((end_config - start_config).norm() > 0.000001)
208  {
209  path_segments_.push_back(std::make_unique<LinearPathSegment>(start_config, end_config));
210  }
211  path_segments_.emplace_back(blend_segment);
212 
213  start_config = blend_segment->getConfig(blend_segment->getLength());
214  }
215  else
216  {
217  path_segments_.push_back(std::make_unique<LinearPathSegment>(start_config, *path_iterator2));
218  start_config = *path_iterator2;
219  }
220  path_iterator1 = path_iterator2;
221  ++path_iterator2;
222  }
223 
224  // Create list of switching point candidates, calculate total path length and
225  // absolute positions of path segments
226  for (std::unique_ptr<PathSegment>& path_segment : path_segments_)
227  {
228  path_segment->position_ = length_;
229  std::list<double> local_switching_points = path_segment->getSwitchingPoints();
230  for (std::list<double>::const_iterator point = local_switching_points.begin();
231  point != local_switching_points.end(); ++point)
232  {
233  switching_points_.push_back(std::make_pair(length_ + *point, false));
234  }
235  length_ += path_segment->getLength();
236  while (!switching_points_.empty() && switching_points_.back().first >= length_)
237  switching_points_.pop_back();
238  switching_points_.push_back(std::make_pair(length_, true));
239  }
240  switching_points_.pop_back();
241 }

243 Path::Path(const Path& path) : length_(path.length_), switching_points_(path.switching_points_)
244 {
245  for (const std::unique_ptr<PathSegment>& path_segment : path.path_segments_)

247  path_segments_.emplace_back(path_segment->clone());
248  }

256 PathSegment* Path::getPathSegment(double& s) const
257 {
258  std::list<std::unique_ptr<PathSegment>>::const_iterator it = path_segments_.begin();
259  std::list<std::unique_ptr<PathSegment>>::const_iterator next = it;
260  ++next;
261  while (next != path_segments_.end() && s >= (*next)->position_)
262  {
263  it = next;
264  ++next;
265  }
266  s -= (*it)->position_;
267  return (*it).get();
268 }

288 double Path::getNextSwitchingPoint(double s, bool& discontinuity) const
289 {
290  std::list<std::pair<double, bool>>::const_iterator it = switching_points_.begin();
291  while (it != switching_points_.end() && it->first <= s)
292  {
293  ++it;
294  }
295  if (it == switching_points_.end())
296  {
297  discontinuity = true;
298  return length_;
299  }
300  discontinuity = it->second;
301  return it->first;
302 }

305 {
306  return switching_points_;

314 Trajectory::Trajectory(const Path& path, const Eigen::VectorXd& max_velocity, const Eigen::VectorXd& max_acceleration,
315  double time_step)
316  : path_(path)
317  , max_velocity_(max_velocity)
318  , max_acceleration_(max_acceleration)
319  , joint_num_(max_velocity.size())
320  , valid_(true)
321  , time_step_(time_step)
322  , cached_time_(std::numeric_limits<double>::max())
323 {
324  trajectory_.push_back(TrajectoryStep(0.0, 0.0));
325  double after_acceleration = getMinMaxPathAcceleration(0.0, 0.0, true);
326  while (valid_ && !integrateForward(trajectory_, after_acceleration) && valid_)
327  {
328  double before_acceleration;
329  TrajectoryStep switching_point;
330  if (getNextSwitchingPoint(trajectory_.back().path_pos_, switching_point, before_acceleration, after_acceleration))
331  {
332  break;
333  }
334  integrateBackward(trajectory_, switching_point.path_pos_, switching_point.path_vel_, before_acceleration);
335  }
336 
337  if (valid_)
338  {
339  double before_acceleration = getMinMaxPathAcceleration(path_.getLength(), 0.0, false);
340  integrateBackward(trajectory_, path_.getLength(), 0.0, before_acceleration);
341  }
342 
343  if (valid_)
344  {
345  // Calculate timing
346  std::list<TrajectoryStep>::iterator previous = trajectory_.begin();
347  std::list<TrajectoryStep>::iterator it = previous;
348  it->time_ = 0.0;
349  ++it;
350  while (it != trajectory_.end())
351  {
352  it->time_ =
353  previous->time_ + (it->path_pos_ - previous->path_pos_) / ((it->path_vel_ + previous->path_vel_) / 2.0);
354  previous = it;
355  ++it;
356  }
357  }
358 }

364 // Returns true if end of path is reached.
365 bool Trajectory::getNextSwitchingPoint(double path_pos, TrajectoryStep& next_switching_point,
366  double& before_acceleration, double& after_acceleration)
367 {
368  TrajectoryStep acceleration_switching_point(path_pos, 0.0);
369  double acceleration_before_acceleration, acceleration_after_acceleration;
370  bool acceleration_reached_end;
371  do
372  {
373  acceleration_reached_end =
374  getNextAccelerationSwitchingPoint(acceleration_switching_point.path_pos_, acceleration_switching_point,
375  acceleration_before_acceleration, acceleration_after_acceleration);
376  } while (!acceleration_reached_end &&
377  acceleration_switching_point.path_vel_ > getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(acceleration_switching_point.path_pos_));
378 
379  TrajectoryStep velocity_switching_point(path_pos, 0.0);
380  double velocity_before_acceleration, velocity_after_acceleration;
381  bool velocity_reached_end;
382  do
383  {
384  velocity_reached_end = getNextVelocitySwitchingPoint(velocity_switching_point.path_pos_, velocity_switching_point,
385  velocity_before_acceleration, velocity_after_acceleration);
386  } while (
387  !velocity_reached_end && velocity_switching_point.path_pos_ <= acceleration_switching_point.path_pos_ &&
388  (velocity_switching_point.path_vel_ > getAccelerationMaxPathVelocity(velocity_switching_point.path_pos_ - EPS) ||
389  velocity_switching_point.path_vel_ > getAccelerationMaxPathVelocity(velocity_switching_point.path_pos_ + EPS)));
390 
391  if (acceleration_reached_end && velocity_reached_end)
392  {
393  return true;
394  }
395  else if (!acceleration_reached_end &&
396  (velocity_reached_end || acceleration_switching_point.path_pos_ <= velocity_switching_point.path_pos_))
397  {
398  next_switching_point = acceleration_switching_point;
399  before_acceleration = acceleration_before_acceleration;
400  after_acceleration = acceleration_after_acceleration;
401  return false;
402  }
403  else
404  {
405  next_switching_point = velocity_switching_point;
406  before_acceleration = velocity_before_acceleration;
407  after_acceleration = velocity_after_acceleration;
408  return false;
409  }
410 }
411 
412 bool Trajectory::getNextAccelerationSwitchingPoint(double path_pos, TrajectoryStep& next_switching_point,
413  double& before_acceleration, double& after_acceleration)
414 {
415  double switching_path_pos = path_pos;
416  double switching_path_vel;
417  while (true)
418  {
419  bool discontinuity;
420  switching_path_pos = path_.getNextSwitchingPoint(switching_path_pos, discontinuity);
421 
422  if (switching_path_pos > path_.getLength() - EPS)
423  {
424  return true;
425  }
426 
427  if (discontinuity)
428  {
429  const double before_path_vel = getAccelerationMaxPathVelocity(switching_path_pos - EPS);
430  const double after_path_vel = getAccelerationMaxPathVelocity(switching_path_pos + EPS);
431  switching_path_vel = std::min(before_path_vel, after_path_vel);
432  before_acceleration = getMinMaxPathAcceleration(switching_path_pos - EPS, switching_path_vel, false);
433  after_acceleration = getMinMaxPathAcceleration(switching_path_pos + EPS, switching_path_vel, true);
434 
435  if ((before_path_vel > after_path_vel ||
436  getMinMaxPhaseSlope(switching_path_pos - EPS, switching_path_vel, false) >
437  getAccelerationMaxPathVelocityDeriv(switching_path_pos - 2.0 * EPS)) &&
438  (before_path_vel < after_path_vel || getMinMaxPhaseSlope(switching_path_pos + EPS, switching_path_vel, true) <
439  getAccelerationMaxPathVelocityDeriv(switching_path_pos + 2.0 * EPS)))
440  {
441  break;
442  }
443  }
444  else
445  {
446  switching_path_vel = getAccelerationMaxPathVelocity(switching_path_pos);
447  before_acceleration = 0.0;
448  after_acceleration = 0.0;
449 
450  if (getAccelerationMaxPathVelocityDeriv(switching_path_pos - EPS) < 0.0 &&
451  getAccelerationMaxPathVelocityDeriv(switching_path_pos + EPS) > 0.0)
452  {
453  break;
454  }
455  }
456  }
457 
458  next_switching_point = TrajectoryStep(switching_path_pos, switching_path_vel);
459  return false;
460 }
461 
462 bool Trajectory::getNextVelocitySwitchingPoint(double path_pos, TrajectoryStep& next_switching_point,
463  double& before_acceleration, double& after_acceleration)
464 {
465  const double step_size = 0.001;
466  const double accuracy = 0.000001;
467 
468  bool start = false;
469  path_pos -= step_size;
470  do
471  {
472  path_pos += step_size;
473 
474  if (getMinMaxPhaseSlope(path_pos, getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(path_pos), false) >=
475  getVelocityMaxPathVelocityDeriv(path_pos))
476  {
477  start = true;
478  }
479  } while ((!start || getMinMaxPhaseSlope(path_pos, getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(path_pos), false) >
480  getVelocityMaxPathVelocityDeriv(path_pos)) &&
481  path_pos < path_.getLength());
482 
483  if (path_pos >= path_.getLength())
484  {
485  return true; // end of trajectory reached
486  }
487 
488  double before_path_pos = path_pos - step_size;
489  double after_path_pos = path_pos;
490  while (after_path_pos - before_path_pos > accuracy)
491  {
492  path_pos = (before_path_pos + after_path_pos) / 2.0;
493  if (getMinMaxPhaseSlope(path_pos, getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(path_pos), false) >
494  getVelocityMaxPathVelocityDeriv(path_pos))
495  {
496  before_path_pos = path_pos;
497  }
498  else
499  {
500  after_path_pos = path_pos;
501  }
502  }
503 
504  before_acceleration = getMinMaxPathAcceleration(before_path_pos, getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(before_path_pos), false);
505  after_acceleration = getMinMaxPathAcceleration(after_path_pos, getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(after_path_pos), true);
506  next_switching_point = TrajectoryStep(after_path_pos, getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(after_path_pos));
507  return false;
508 }

510 // Returns true if end of path is reached
511 bool Trajectory::integrateForward(std::list<TrajectoryStep>& trajectory, double acceleration)
512 {
513  double path_pos = trajectory.back().path_pos_;
514  double path_vel = trajectory.back().path_vel_;
515 
516  std::list<std::pair<double, bool>> switching_points = path_.getSwitchingPoints();
517  std::list<std::pair<double, bool>>::iterator next_discontinuity = switching_points.begin();
518 
519  while (true)
520  {
521  while ((next_discontinuity != switching_points.end()) &&
522  (next_discontinuity->first <= path_pos || !next_discontinuity->second))
523  {
524  ++next_discontinuity;
525  }
526 
527  double old_path_pos = path_pos;
528  double old_path_vel = path_vel;
529 
530  path_vel += time_step_ * acceleration;
531  path_pos += time_step_ * 0.5 * (old_path_vel + path_vel);
532 
533  if (next_discontinuity != switching_points.end() && path_pos > next_discontinuity->first)
534  {
535  // Avoid having a TrajectoryStep with path_pos near a switching point which will cause an almost identical
536  // TrajectoryStep get added in the next run (https://github.com/ros-planning/moveit/issues/1665)
537  if (path_pos - next_discontinuity->first < EPS)
538  {
539  continue;
540  }
541  path_vel = old_path_vel +
542  (next_discontinuity->first - old_path_pos) * (path_vel - old_path_vel) / (path_pos - old_path_pos);
543  path_pos = next_discontinuity->first;
544  }
545 
546  if (path_pos > path_.getLength())
547  {
548  trajectory.push_back(TrajectoryStep(path_pos, path_vel));
549  return true;
550  }
551  else if (path_vel < 0.0)
552  {
553  valid_ = false;
554  ROS_ERROR_NAMED(LOGNAME, "Error while integrating forward: Negative path velocity");
555  return true;
556  }
557 
558  if (path_vel > getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(path_pos) &&
559  getMinMaxPhaseSlope(old_path_pos, getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(old_path_pos), false) <=
560  getVelocityMaxPathVelocityDeriv(old_path_pos))
561  {
562  path_vel = getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(path_pos);
563  }
564 
565  trajectory.push_back(TrajectoryStep(path_pos, path_vel));
566  acceleration = getMinMaxPathAcceleration(path_pos, path_vel, true);
567 
568  if (path_vel > getAccelerationMaxPathVelocity(path_pos) || path_vel > getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(path_pos))
569  {
570  // Find more accurate intersection with max-velocity curve using bisection
571  TrajectoryStep overshoot = trajectory.back();
572  trajectory.pop_back();
573  double before = trajectory.back().path_pos_;
574  double before_path_vel = trajectory.back().path_vel_;
575  double after = overshoot.path_pos_;
576  double after_path_vel = overshoot.path_vel_;
577  while (after - before > EPS)
578  {
579  const double midpoint = 0.5 * (before + after);
580  double midpoint_path_vel = 0.5 * (before_path_vel + after_path_vel);
581 
582  if (midpoint_path_vel > getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(midpoint) &&
583  getMinMaxPhaseSlope(before, getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(before), false) <=
584  getVelocityMaxPathVelocityDeriv(before))
585  {
586  midpoint_path_vel = getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(midpoint);
587  }
588 
589  if (midpoint_path_vel > getAccelerationMaxPathVelocity(midpoint) ||
590  midpoint_path_vel > getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(midpoint))
591  {
592  after = midpoint;
593  after_path_vel = midpoint_path_vel;
594  }
595  else
596  {
597  before = midpoint;
598  before_path_vel = midpoint_path_vel;
599  }
600  }
601  trajectory.push_back(TrajectoryStep(before, before_path_vel));
602 
603  if (getAccelerationMaxPathVelocity(after) < getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(after))
604  {
605  if (after > next_discontinuity->first)
606  {
607  return false;
608  }
609  else if (getMinMaxPhaseSlope(trajectory.back().path_pos_, trajectory.back().path_vel_, true) >
610  getAccelerationMaxPathVelocityDeriv(trajectory.back().path_pos_))
611  {
612  return false;
613  }
614  }
615  else
616  {
617  if (getMinMaxPhaseSlope(trajectory.back().path_pos_, trajectory_.back().path_vel_, false) >
618  getVelocityMaxPathVelocityDeriv(trajectory_.back().path_pos_))
619  {
620  return false;
621  }
622  }
623  }
624  }
625 }
626 
627 void Trajectory::integrateBackward(std::list<TrajectoryStep>& start_trajectory, double path_pos, double path_vel,
628  double acceleration)
629 {
630  std::list<TrajectoryStep>::iterator start2 = start_trajectory.end();
631  --start2;
632  std::list<TrajectoryStep>::iterator start1 = start2;
633  --start1;
634  std::list<TrajectoryStep> trajectory;
635  double slope;
636  assert(start1->path_pos_ <= path_pos);
637 
638  while (start1 != start_trajectory.begin() || path_pos >= 0.0)
639  {
640  if (start1->path_pos_ <= path_pos)
641  {
642  trajectory.push_front(TrajectoryStep(path_pos, path_vel));
643  path_vel -= time_step_ * acceleration;
644  path_pos -= time_step_ * 0.5 * (path_vel + trajectory.front().path_vel_);
645  acceleration = getMinMaxPathAcceleration(path_pos, path_vel, false);
646  slope = (trajectory.front().path_vel_ - path_vel) / (trajectory.front().path_pos_ - path_pos);
647 
648  if (path_vel < 0.0)
649  {
650  valid_ = false;
651  ROS_ERROR_NAMED(LOGNAME, "Error while integrating backward: Negative path velocity");
652  end_trajectory_ = trajectory;
653  return;
654  }
655  }
656  else
657  {
658  --start1;
659  --start2;
660  }
661 
662  // Check for intersection between current start trajectory and backward
663  // trajectory segments
664  const double start_slope = (start2->path_vel_ - start1->path_vel_) / (start2->path_pos_ - start1->path_pos_);
665  const double intersection_path_pos =
666  (start1->path_vel_ - path_vel + slope * path_pos - start_slope * start1->path_pos_) / (slope - start_slope);
667  if (std::max(start1->path_pos_, path_pos) - EPS <= intersection_path_pos &&
668  intersection_path_pos <= EPS + std::min(start2->path_pos_, trajectory.front().path_pos_))
669  {
670  const double intersection_path_vel =
671  start1->path_vel_ + start_slope * (intersection_path_pos - start1->path_pos_);
672  start_trajectory.erase(start2, start_trajectory.end());
673  start_trajectory.push_back(TrajectoryStep(intersection_path_pos, intersection_path_vel));
674  start_trajectory.splice(start_trajectory.end(), trajectory);
675  return;
676  }
677  }
678 
679  valid_ = false;
680  ROS_ERROR_NAMED(LOGNAME, "Error while integrating backward: Did not hit start trajectory");
681  end_trajectory_ = trajectory;
682 }
683 
684 double Trajectory::getMinMaxPathAcceleration(double path_pos, double path_vel, bool max)
685 {
686  Eigen::VectorXd config_deriv = path_.getTangent(path_pos);
687  Eigen::VectorXd config_deriv2 = path_.getCurvature(path_pos);
688  double factor = max ? 1.0 : -1.0;
689  double max_path_acceleration = std::numeric_limits<double>::max();
690  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < joint_num_; ++i)
691  {
692  if (config_deriv[i] != 0.0)
693  {
694  max_path_acceleration =
695  std::min(max_path_acceleration, max_acceleration_[i] / std::abs(config_deriv[i]) -
696  factor * config_deriv2[i] * path_vel * path_vel / config_deriv[i]);
697  }
698  }
699  return factor * max_path_acceleration;
700 }
701 
702 double Trajectory::getMinMaxPhaseSlope(double path_pos, double path_vel, bool max)
703 {
704  return getMinMaxPathAcceleration(path_pos, path_vel, max) / path_vel;
705 }
706 
707 double Trajectory::getAccelerationMaxPathVelocity(double path_pos) const
708 {
709  double max_path_velocity = std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity();
710  const Eigen::VectorXd config_deriv = path_.getTangent(path_pos);
711  const Eigen::VectorXd config_deriv2 = path_.getCurvature(path_pos);
712  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < joint_num_; ++i)
713  {
714  if (config_deriv[i] != 0.0)
715  {
716  for (unsigned int j = i + 1; j < joint_num_; ++j)
717  {
718  if (config_deriv[j] != 0.0)
719  {
720  double a_ij = config_deriv2[i] / config_deriv[i] - config_deriv2[j] / config_deriv[j];
721  if (a_ij != 0.0)
722  {
723  max_path_velocity = std::min(max_path_velocity, sqrt((max_acceleration_[i] / std::abs(config_deriv[i]) +
724  max_acceleration_[j] / std::abs(config_deriv[j])) /
725  std::abs(a_ij)));
726  }
727  }
728  }
729  }
730  else if (config_deriv2[i] != 0.0)
731  {
732  max_path_velocity = std::min(max_path_velocity, sqrt(max_acceleration_[i] / std::abs(config_deriv2[i])));
733  }
734  }
735  return max_path_velocity;
736 }
737 
738 double Trajectory::getVelocityMaxPathVelocity(double path_pos) const
739 {
740  const Eigen::VectorXd tangent = path_.getTangent(path_pos);
741  double max_path_velocity = std::numeric_limits<double>::max();
742  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < joint_num_; ++i)
743  {
744  max_path_velocity = std::min(max_path_velocity, max_velocity_[i] / std::abs(tangent[i]));
745  }
746  return max_path_velocity;
747 }
748 
749 double Trajectory::getAccelerationMaxPathVelocityDeriv(double path_pos)
750 {
751  return (getAccelerationMaxPathVelocity(path_pos + EPS) - getAccelerationMaxPathVelocity(path_pos - EPS)) /
752  (2.0 * EPS);
753 }
754 
755 double Trajectory::getVelocityMaxPathVelocityDeriv(double path_pos)
756 {
757  const Eigen::VectorXd tangent = path_.getTangent(path_pos);
758  double max_path_velocity = std::numeric_limits<double>::max();
759  unsigned int active_constraint;
760  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < joint_num_; ++i)
761  {
762  const double this_max_path_velocity = max_velocity_[i] / std::abs(tangent[i]);
763  if (this_max_path_velocity < max_path_velocity)
764  {
765  max_path_velocity = this_max_path_velocity;
766  active_constraint = i;
767  }
768  }
769  return -(max_velocity_[active_constraint] * path_.getCurvature(path_pos)[active_constraint]) /
770  (tangent[active_constraint] * std::abs(tangent[active_constraint]));
771 }

783 std::list<Trajectory::TrajectoryStep>::const_iterator Trajectory::getTrajectorySegment(double time) const
784 {
785  if (time >= trajectory_.back().time_)
786  {
787  std::list<TrajectoryStep>::const_iterator last = trajectory_.end();
788  last--;
789  return last;
790  }
791  else
792  {
793  if (time < cached_time_)
794  {
795  cached_trajectory_segment_ = trajectory_.begin();
796  }
797  while (time >= cached_trajectory_segment_->time_)
798  {
799  ++cached_trajectory_segment_;
800  }
801  cached_time_ = time;
802  return cached_trajectory_segment_;
803  }
804 }

806 Eigen::VectorXd Trajectory::getPosition(double time) const
807 {
808  std::list<TrajectoryStep>::const_iterator it = getTrajectorySegment(time);
809  std::list<TrajectoryStep>::const_iterator previous = it;
810  previous--;
811 
812  double time_step = it->time_ - previous->time_;
813  const double acceleration =
814  2.0 * (it->path_pos_ - previous->path_pos_ - time_step * previous->path_vel_) / (time_step * time_step);
815 
816  time_step = time - previous->time_;
817  const double path_pos =
818  previous->path_pos_ + time_step * previous->path_vel_ + 0.5 * time_step * time_step * acceleration;
819 
820  return path_.getConfig(path_pos);
821 }
822 
823 Eigen::VectorXd Trajectory::getVelocity(double time) const
824 {
825  std::list<TrajectoryStep>::const_iterator it = getTrajectorySegment(time);
826  std::list<TrajectoryStep>::const_iterator previous = it;
827  previous--;
828 
829  double time_step = it->time_ - previous->time_;
830  const double acceleration =
831  2.0 * (it->path_pos_ - previous->path_pos_ - time_step * previous->path_vel_) / (time_step * time_step);
832 
833  time_step = time - previous->time_;
834  const double path_pos =
835  previous->path_pos_ + time_step * previous->path_vel_ + 0.5 * time_step * time_step * acceleration;
836  const double path_vel = previous->path_vel_ + time_step * acceleration;
837 
838  return path_.getTangent(path_pos) * path_vel;
839 }
840 
841 Eigen::VectorXd Trajectory::getAcceleration(double time) const
842 {
843  std::list<TrajectoryStep>::const_iterator it = getTrajectorySegment(time);
844  std::list<TrajectoryStep>::const_iterator previous = it;
845  previous--;
846 
847  double time_step = it->time_ - previous->time_;
848  const double acceleration =
849  2.0 * (it->path_pos_ - previous->path_pos_ - time_step * previous->path_vel_) / (time_step * time_step);
850 
851  time_step = time - previous->time_;
852  const double path_pos =
853  previous->path_pos_ + time_step * previous->path_vel_ + 0.5 * time_step * time_step * acceleration;
854  const double path_vel = previous->path_vel_ + time_step * acceleration;
855  Eigen::VectorXd path_acc =
856  (path_.getTangent(path_pos) * path_vel - path_.getTangent(previous->path_pos_) * previous->path_vel_);
857  if (time_step > 0.0)
858  path_acc /= time_step;
859  return path_acc;
860 }

872 bool TimeOptimalTrajectoryGeneration::computeTimeStamps(robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectory& trajectory,
873  const double max_velocity_scaling_factor,
874  const double max_acceleration_scaling_factor) const
875 {
876  if (trajectory.empty())
877  return true;
878 
879  const moveit::core::JointModelGroup* group = trajectory.getGroup();
880  if (!group)
881  {
882  ROS_ERROR_NAMED(LOGNAME, "It looks like the planner did not set the group the plan was computed for");
883  return false;
884  }
885 
886  // Validate scaling
887  double velocity_scaling_factor = 1.0;
888  if (max_velocity_scaling_factor > 0.0 && max_velocity_scaling_factor <= 1.0)
889  {
890  velocity_scaling_factor = max_velocity_scaling_factor;
891  }
892  else if (max_velocity_scaling_factor == 0.0)
893  {
894  ROS_DEBUG_NAMED(LOGNAME, "A max_velocity_scaling_factor of 0.0 was specified, defaulting to %f instead.",
895  velocity_scaling_factor);
896  }
897  else
898  {
899  ROS_WARN_NAMED(LOGNAME, "Invalid max_velocity_scaling_factor %f specified, defaulting to %f instead.",
900  max_velocity_scaling_factor, velocity_scaling_factor);
901  }
902 
903  double acceleration_scaling_factor = 1.0;
904  if (max_acceleration_scaling_factor > 0.0 && max_acceleration_scaling_factor <= 1.0)
905  {
906  acceleration_scaling_factor = max_acceleration_scaling_factor;
907  }
908  else if (max_acceleration_scaling_factor == 0.0)
909  {
910  ROS_DEBUG_NAMED(LOGNAME, "A max_acceleration_scaling_factor of 0.0 was specified, defaulting to %f instead.",
911  acceleration_scaling_factor);
912  }
913  else
914  {
915  ROS_WARN_NAMED(LOGNAME, "Invalid max_acceleration_scaling_factor %f specified, defaulting to %f instead.",
916  max_acceleration_scaling_factor, acceleration_scaling_factor);
917  }
918 
919  // This lib does not actually work properly when angles wrap around, so we need to unwind the path first
920  trajectory.unwind();
921 
922  // This is pretty much copied from IterativeParabolicTimeParameterization::applyVelocityConstraints
923  const std::vector<std::string>& vars = group->getVariableNames();
924  const std::vector<int>& idx = group->getVariableIndexList();
925  const moveit::core::RobotModel& rmodel = group->getParentModel();
926  const unsigned num_joints = group->getVariableCount();
927  const unsigned num_points = trajectory.getWayPointCount();
928 
929  // Get the limits (we do this at same time, unlike IterativeParabolicTimeParameterization)
930  Eigen::VectorXd max_velocity(num_joints);
931  Eigen::VectorXd max_acceleration(num_joints);
932  for (size_t j = 0; j < num_joints; ++j)
933  {
934  const moveit::core::VariableBounds& bounds = rmodel.getVariableBounds(vars[j]);
935 
936  // Limits need to be non-zero, otherwise we never exit
937  max_velocity[j] = 1.0;
938  if (bounds.velocity_bounded_)
939  {
940  max_velocity[j] =
941  std::min(std::fabs(bounds.max_velocity_), std::fabs(bounds.min_velocity_)) * velocity_scaling_factor;
942  max_velocity[j] = std::max(0.01, max_velocity[j]);
943  }
944 
945  max_acceleration[j] = 1.0;
946  if (bounds.acceleration_bounded_)
947  {
948  max_acceleration[j] = std::min(std::fabs(bounds.max_acceleration_), std::fabs(bounds.min_acceleration_)) *
949  acceleration_scaling_factor;
950  max_acceleration[j] = std::max(0.01, max_acceleration[j]);
951  }
952  }
953 
954  // Have to convert into Eigen data structs and remove repeated points
955  // (https://github.com/tobiaskunz/trajectories/issues/3)
956  std::list<Eigen::VectorXd> points;
957  for (size_t p = 0; p < num_points; ++p)
958  {
959  moveit::core::RobotStatePtr waypoint = trajectory.getWayPointPtr(p);
960  Eigen::VectorXd new_point(num_joints);
961  // The first point should always be kept
962  bool diverse_point = (p == 0);
963 
964  for (size_t j = 0; j < num_joints; ++j)
965  {
966  new_point[j] = waypoint->getVariablePosition(idx[j]);
967  // If any joint angle is different, it's a unique waypoint
968  if (p > 0 && std::fabs(new_point[j] - points.back()[j]) > min_angle_change_)
969  {
970  diverse_point = true;
971  }
972  }
973 
974  if (diverse_point)
975  points.push_back(new_point);
976  }
977 
978  // Return trajectory with only the first waypoint if there are not multiple diverse points
979  if (points.size() == 1)
980  {
981  ROS_DEBUG_NAMED(LOGNAME,
982  "Trajectory is parameterized with 0.0 dynamics since it only contains a single distinct waypoint.");
983  moveit::core::RobotState waypoint = moveit::core::RobotState(trajectory.getWayPoint(0));
984  waypoint.zeroVelocities();
985  waypoint.zeroAccelerations();
986  trajectory.clear();
987  trajectory.addSuffixWayPoint(waypoint, 0.0);
988  return true;
989  }
990 
991  // Now actually call the algorithm
992  Trajectory parameterized(Path(points, path_tolerance_), max_velocity, max_acceleration, 0.001);
993  if (!parameterized.isValid())
994  {
995  ROS_ERROR_NAMED(LOGNAME, "Unable to parameterize trajectory.");
996  return false;
997  }
998 
999  // Compute sample count
1000  size_t sample_count = std::ceil(parameterized.getDuration() / resample_dt_);
1001 
1002  // Resample and fill in trajectory
1003  moveit::core::RobotState waypoint = moveit::core::RobotState(trajectory.getWayPoint(0));
1004  trajectory.clear();
1005  double last_t = 0;
1006  for (size_t sample = 0; sample <= sample_count; ++sample)
1007  {
1008  // always sample the end of the trajectory as well
1009  double t = std::min(parameterized.getDuration(), sample * resample_dt_);
1010  Eigen::VectorXd position = parameterized.getPosition(t);
1011  Eigen::VectorXd velocity = parameterized.getVelocity(t);
1012  Eigen::VectorXd acceleration = parameterized.getAcceleration(t);
1013 
1014  for (size_t j = 0; j < num_joints; ++j)
1015  {
1016  waypoint.setVariablePosition(idx[j], position[j]);
1017  waypoint.setVariableVelocity(idx[j], velocity[j]);
1018  waypoint.setVariableAcceleration(idx[j], acceleration[j]);
1019  }
1020 
1021  trajectory.addSuffixWayPoint(waypoint, t - last_t);
1022  last_t = t;
1023  }
1024 
1025  return true;
1026 }
1027 } // namespace trajectory_processing
